{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1206,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":14325,"text":"These bees are in my backyard\nin Berkeley, California."},{"time":18822,"text":"Until last year,\nI'd never kept bees before,"},{"time":21221,"text":"but National Geographic asked me\nto photograph a story about them,"},{"time":25270,"text":"and I decided, to be able\nto take compelling images,"},{"time":27769,"text":"I should start keeping bees myself."},{"time":30253,"text":"And as you may know,"},{"time":31948,"text":"bees pollinate one third\nof our food crops,"},{"time":34572,"text":"and lately they've been having\na really hard time."},{"time":37730,"text":"So as a photographer, I wanted to explore\nwhat this problem really looks like."},{"time":42281,"text":"So I'm going to show you\nwhat I found over the last year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46276,"text":"This furry little creature"},{"time":47900,"text":"is a fresh young bee halfway emerged\nfrom its brood cell,"},{"time":52243,"text":"and bees right now are dealing\nwith several different problems,"},{"time":55283,"text":"including pesticides, diseases,\nand habitat loss,"},{"time":59535,"text":"but the single greatest threat\nis a parasitic mite from Asia,"},{"time":64146,"text":"Varroa destructor."},{"time":66475,"text":"And this pinhead-sized mite\ncrawls onto young bees"},{"time":69354,"text":"and sucks their blood."},{"time":71699,"text":"This eventually destroys a hive"},{"time":73696,"text":"because it weakens\nthe immune system of the bees,"},{"time":76940,"text":"and it makes them more vulnerable\nto stress and disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81776,"text":"Now, bees are the most sensitive"},{"time":83773,"text":"when they're developing\ninside their brood cells,"},{"time":86513,"text":"and I wanted to know\nwhat that process really looks like,"},{"time":89624,"text":"so I teamed up\nwith a bee lab at U.C. Davis"},{"time":92248,"text":"and figured out how to raise bees\nin front of a camera."},{"time":95993,"text":"I'm going to show you\nthe first 21 days of a bee's life"},{"time":98981,"text":"condensed into 60 seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103763,"text":"This is a bee egg\nas it hatches into a larva,"},{"time":108567,"text":"and those newly hatched larvae\nswim around their cells"},{"time":113012,"text":"feeding on this white goo\nthat nurse bees secrete for them."},{"time":119616,"text":"Then, their head and their legs\nslowly differentiate"},{"time":124159,"text":"as they transform into pupae."},{"time":129833,"text":"Here's that same pupation process,"},{"time":131853,"text":"and you can actually see the mites\nrunning around in the cells."},{"time":135243,"text":"Then the tissue in their body reorganizes"},{"time":139510,"text":"and the pigment slowly\ndevelops in their eyes."},{"time":146869,"text":"The last step of the process\nis their skin shrivels up"},{"time":152757,"text":"and they sprout hair."},{"time":155245,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168805,"text":"So -- (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":174703,"text":"As you can see halfway\nthrough that video,"},{"time":177907,"text":"the mites were running around\non the baby bees,"},{"time":180461,"text":"and the way that beekeepers\ntypically manage these mites"},{"time":184390,"text":"is they treat their hives with chemicals."},{"time":187404,"text":"In the long run, that's bad news,"},{"time":189670,"text":"so researchers are working\non finding alternatives"},{"time":193223,"text":"to control these mites."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196195,"text":"This is one of those alternatives."},{"time":198963,"text":"It's an experimental breeding program\nat the USDA Bee Lab in Baton Rouge,"},{"time":203328,"text":"and this queen and her attendant bees\nare part of that program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207735,"text":"Now, the researchers figured out"},{"time":211430,"text":"that some of the bees have\na natural ability to fight mites,"},{"time":215152,"text":"so they set out to breed\na line of mite-resistant bees."},{"time":220782,"text":"This is what it takes\nto breed bees in a lab."},{"time":223418,"text":"The virgin queen is sedated"},{"time":226158,"text":"and then artificially inseminated\nusing this precision instrument."},{"time":231200,"text":"Now, this procedure allows the researchers"},{"time":233478,"text":"to control exactly\nwhich bees are being crossed,"},{"time":238500,"text":"but there's a tradeoff\nin having this much control."},{"time":241627,"text":"They succeeded in breeding\nmite-resistant bees,"},{"time":244832,"text":"but in that process, those bees\nstarted to lose traits"},{"time":247920,"text":"like their gentleness\nand their ability to store honey,"},{"time":251685,"text":"so to overcome that problem,"},{"time":254194,"text":"these researchers are now collaborating\nwith commercial beekeepers."},{"time":258252,"text":"This is Bret Adee opening\none of his 72,000 beehives."},{"time":263120,"text":"He and his brother run the largest\nbeekeeping operation in the world,"},{"time":267750,"text":"and the USDA is integrating their\nmite-resistant bees into his operation"},{"time":273409,"text":"with the hope that over time,"},{"time":275052,"text":"they'll be able to select the bees\nthat are not only mite-resistant"},{"time":278723,"text":"but also retain all of these qualities\nthat make them useful to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284165,"text":"And to say it like that"},{"time":285860,"text":"makes it sound like we're manipulating\nand exploiting bees,"},{"time":289157,"text":"and the truth is, we've been doing that\nfor thousands of years."},{"time":292593,"text":"We took this wild creature\nand put it inside of a box,"},{"time":297747,"text":"practically domesticating it,"},{"time":299861,"text":"and originally that was\nso that we could harvest their honey,"},{"time":303970,"text":"but over time we started losing\nour native pollinators,"},{"time":306725,"text":"our wild pollinators,"},{"time":308420,"text":"and there are many places now\nwhere those wild pollinators"},{"time":311485,"text":"can no longer meet the pollination\ndemands of our agriculture,"},{"time":315284,"text":"so these managed bees have become\nan integral part of our food system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320508,"text":"So when people talk about saving bees,"},{"time":323227,"text":"my interpretation of that"},{"time":325360,"text":"is we need to save\nour relationship to bees,"},{"time":328588,"text":"and in order to design new solutions,"},{"time":333592,"text":"we have to understand\nthe basic biology of bees"},{"time":338693,"text":"and understand the effects\nof stressors that we sometimes cannot see."},{"time":345909,"text":"In other words, we have\nto understand bees up close."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349114,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351384,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}